  ],
  "text": "The LibreOffice document model architecture is built on a hierarchy of document shell classes managed by the application framework. SfxObjectShell (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx) is the base document shell class that serves as the foundation for all document types. All LibreOffice application documents inherit from this class.\n\nEach LibreOffice module implements its own document class derived from or working with SfxObjectShell:\n- Writer documents use SwDoc (sw/inc/doc.hxx), which represents a word processing document with text content, formatting, and writer-specific features.\n- Calc documents use ScDocument (sc/inc/document.hxx), which manages spreadsheet data structures including cells, sheets, formulas, and calculations.\n- Impress/Draw documents use SdDrawDocument (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx), which handles presentation and drawing document structure including slides, shapes, and drawing objects.\n\nThe overall application framework is coordinated by SfxApplication (sfx2/inc/appl.hxx), which serves as the entry point and coordinator for the LibreOffice application framework, managing multiple document instances and the application lifecycle."
}

